# Functions Package

AWS Lambda functions triggered by various events (S3, API Gateway, etc.).

## Structure

```
src/
├── myFunction.ts    # Lambda handler
└── anotherFunc.ts   # Another Lambda handler
```

## Lambda Handler Pattern

```typescript
import { S3Event } from "aws-lambda";
// or other event types: APIGatewayProxyEvent, SQSEvent, etc.

export const handler = async (event: S3Event) => {
  try {
    // Process the event
    const bucket = event.Records?.[0]?.s3?.bucket?.name;
    const key = event.Records?.[0]?.s3?.object?.key;

    // Your logic here

    return {
      statusCode: 200,
      body: JSON.stringify({ message: "Success" }),
    };
  } catch (error) {
    console.error("Error:", error);
    throw error;
  }
};
```

## Configuration

Lambda functions are configured in `infra/` using SST:

```typescript
// infra/myFunction.ts
new sst.aws.Function("MyFunction", {
  runtime: "nodejs22.x",
  handler: "packages/functions/src/myFunction.handler",
  timeout: "30 seconds",
  environment: {
    API_URL: backendUrl,
  },
});
```

## Dependencies

Add dependencies to this package using:

```bash
yarn workspace @sparrow-template/functions add <package>
```

## Environment Variables

Access via `process.env`:

```typescript
const apiUrl = process.env.API_URL;
```

Environment variables are set in the SST infrastructure configuration.

## Types

Use `@types/aws-lambda` for Lambda event types:

- `S3Event` - S3 bucket triggers
- `APIGatewayProxyEvent` - API Gateway triggers
- `SQSEvent` - SQS queue triggers
- `ScheduledEvent` - CloudWatch scheduled events
